14/09/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- BiH prosecutors on Monday (13 September) indicted an Iraqi-born mujahedeen for war crimes committed in Travnik during the 1992-1995 conflict. Abdulladhim Maktouf was charged with participating in the October 1993 abduction and imprisonment of five Serb civilians, one of whom was later beheaded. John MacNair, a prosecutor heading a department that handles organised crime and corruption cases, told reporters that this is the first in a series of indictments his office plans to issue. 
In other news Monday, the Federation of BiH's (FBiH) Interior Ministry announced it is searching for Dalibor Jelic, 31, a Croat charged with involvement in at least 11 bomb attacks in Sarajevo and Mostar. FBiH police say he is also wanted by Interpol, but refused to provide details. (Dnevni avaz, Nezavisne novine - 14/09/04; AFP, PBS BiH, Pincom.info - 13/09/04) 
